  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Armajaro Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IFC is considering a loan of up to $30 million to Armajaro Trading Group Limited (ATGL or Armajaro).  ATGL is an intermediary holding company and owns 100% of Armajaro Trading Limited (ATL), which was founded in 1998 and is an integrated supply chain manager of soft commodities including cocoa, coffee and, more recently, sugar. ATL aims to be partner of choice in the Agri-commodity supply chain. The proposed investment will scale up ATLs upcountry sourcing capabilities in the origin countries, improve its funding flexibility, strengthen its balance sheet and assist more farmers achieve sustainable farming practices.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project&apos;&apos;s development impact includes direct benefits to rural populations in many developing countries in Africa and Asia and a demonstration impact on sustainability and traceability initiatives. Some key impacts will be: 1)  increased number of farmers reached/trained, 2) improved E&amp;S practices in the traceable portion of the supply chain 3)  improved farmers&apos;&apos; income through certification, training and improved access to market.</narrative>
  </description>
